<event name="ROCK_RAVINE" unique="true">
	<text>On the surface of a nearby planet is a massive ravine. It all looks normal until you spot two Rock scouts flying past, deeper into the ravine.</text>
	<img back="BACK_EVENT_ROCKRAVINE" planet="NONE"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Follow them.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You trail the ships from far behind, making sure they can't see you but never losing them. Not too long after you reach a fork in the ravine, and the ships split up. If you don't want the Rebel fleet catching up, you'll only have time to explore one of the paths.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Follow the ship to the left.</text> <!--FACILITY-->
				<event>
					<text>The ship stops at what looks like a giant facility built into the face of the ravine's sheer drop. With nowhere to hide, the Rockmen inevitably spot you and prepare to defend whatever the facility may be.</text>
					<ship load="SHIP_ROCK_RAVINE_LEFT" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>					
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Follow the ship to the right.</text> <!--WAR CAMP-->
				<event>
					<text>The ship lands near a giant prison camp built on the floor of the ravine. It looks abandoned, but you don't have much time to investigate before the Rockmen spot your ship and attacks.</text>
					<ship load="SHIP_ROCK_RAVINE_RIGHT" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>	
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Nevermind, this is a bad idea.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore the ships.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Those Rockmen could be doing anything down there, and it's none of your business.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="ROCK_RAVINE_LEFT">
	<text>You've defeated the Rock vessel. You have some time to scrap the ship before investigating the facility.</text>
	<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>The entrance to the structure leads you to a deprecated lobby. A barely functional elevator suggests there must be a back-up generator running, because this facility has long since been abandoned. There's several different options for floors to explore, but you'll only have time for one.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Explore the floor marked as "control."</text>
				<event>
					<text>A floor marked control in a Rock facility is sure to be an interesting experience. You head there, wary of the elevator. Inside is a no-longer functional Mind Control system and a giant screen overlooking what looks to be a giant prison camp on the other side of the ravine. You begin to think there's nothing of actual use in this room until you notice a combat augment in the corner, as well as some discarded fuel cells.</text>
					<autoReward level="MED">fuel_only</autoReward>
					<augment name="GIFTLIST_AUGMENT_COMBAT"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Explore the floor marked as "security."</text>
				<event>
					<text>The security floor has piqued your interest. You head there, wary of the elevator. Heavy blast doors protect the way in, but something has managed to bend them back far enough for you to squeeze by. Several monitors overlooks the other rooms of the facility, proving it to be completely empty of staff. Not much here is of value to a military ship, other than a Long-Ranged Scanners augmentation and some droneparts.</text>
					<autoReward level="MED">droneparts_only</autoReward>
					<augment name="ADV_SCANNERS"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Explore the floor marked as "armory."</text>
				<event>
					<text>The armory seems like the obvious choice. You head there, wary of the elevator. Inside you find several racks of supplies and various weapons. With limited manpower, you take one of the weapons at random as well as a few missiles.</text>
					<autoReward level="MED">missiles_only</autoReward>
					<weapon name="RANDOM"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="ROCK_RAVINE_RIGHT">
	<text>You've defeated the Rock vessel. You have some time to scrap the ship before investigating the camp.</text>
	<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Rock prison camp appears to be primarily abandoned, but a lone camp fire that's still burning suggests there may still be some life left behind. You're proven correct when further exploration reveals a small band of prisoners of various races. They explain that the prisoners revolted and managed to kill off most of the Rock guards. The Rockmen retreated and the surviving prisoners starved to death. This small group are the only ones who remain. You don't have enough space on the ship to take them all with you, but you can probably bring one of them.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Bring one of the Rock prisoners.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The Rock bears the markings of an outcast, likely a fugitive from the Rock government who was recently captured. They don't speak much, but you can tell they're glad you've chosen to rescue them.</text>
					<crewMember amount="1" class="outcast"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Bring one of the Human prisoners.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The human turns out to be a Rebel Engineer, captured by the Rockmen with the intent to be used as a hostage to bargain with the Rebels. Unfortunately for them, the Rebels had no interest in buying back the prisoner. They were locked into this camp. Despite being of Rebel origins, they are more than glad to come with you and leave behind this place.</text>
					<crewMember amount="1" class="engineer"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Bring one of the Slug prisoners.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The Slug was a tourist captured by the Rockmen based purely on suspicion. Not wanting to admit to their mistake, they simply chose to lock the Slug away in this prison for the rest of eternity. They're vibrant with energy at the prospect of finally being free.</text>
					<crewMember amount="1" class="slug"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="ROCK_ASTEROID_COLONY" unique="true">
	<text>It appears complete chaos has broken out on the nearby Rock colony. It seems a large asteroid collided with the planet and caused extreme damage, and now hundreds of ships are swarming back and forth from the planet's surface.</text>
	<img planet="PLANET_POPULATED"/>
