	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>Along with the Rockmen comes Stonewall himself, extremely irate at the damage you caused. "What have you done! You have proven your point, everywhere you go you only bring destruction and disrupt our ways of life! What is it that you want, why have you come here to ruin this day? Will simple money be enough to make you leave?"</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Accept their pay.</text>
				<event>
					<text>Reluctantly, the Rock soldiers put down their guns and a hefty sum of scrap is brought out for you. This won't have much lasting effect on the Rock government other than an increase in security, but atleast this will help with your primary mission.</text>
					<autoReward level="MED">scrap_only</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Use Stonewall as a hostage and bargain for an even greater reward.</text>
				<event load="ROCK_HOMEWORLDS_VICTORY_HOSTAGE"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>We came here to make a change. Assassinate Stonewall now.</text>
				<event load="ROCK_HOMEWORLDS_VICTORY_KILL"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<eventList name="ROCK_HOMEWORLDS_VICTORY_HOSTAGE">
	<event>
		<text>You're far quicker than any of the guards, and in only a couple of seconds your blaster is held directly against Stonewall's head. It's a dangerous and nerve-racking exchange, but everything goes as 'planned' and a Rock transport delivers a large supply of goods.</text>
		<autoReward level="HIGH">weapon</autoReward>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>It was a risky move, and things don't go nearly as 'planned'. The Rock guards are quicker than anticipated and one of your crew is shot in the chest. You still manage to grab Stonewall around his massive neck and hold a blaster to his moss-covered face. As your crew lies dying on the floor, a Rock transport is called in to deliver the larger amount of supplies. Once you're satisfied, you hurry back to the ship, making sure to keep your gun pointed at Stonewall the entire way back.</text>
		<autoReward level="HIGH">weapon</autoReward>
		<choice hidden="true" req="medbay" lvl="2">
			<text>(Upg. Medbay) Provide medical assistance to your crew.</text>
			<event>
				<text>Luckily your crew is able to be treated in time. You pull away from the city, glad at the success of the mission.</text>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>There's nothing we can do to save our crew.</text>
			<event>
				<text>Your crew perishes in front of you, a casualty that could have been prevented if you simply hadn't tried something so daring.</text>
				<removeCrew>
					<clone>true</clone>
					<text>Luckily your crew is cloned, relieving you of some of your guilt.</text>
				</removeCrew>
			</event>
		</choice>
	</event>
</eventList>
<event name="ROCK_HOMEWORLDS_VICTORY_KILL">
	<text>You swiftly draw your blaster and blast Stonewall straight in the chest. The mighty titan of a creature falls to the ground in a thud, and the Rock soldiers are sent into chaos. You rush back to the ship but are stopped by the surge of Rock citizens breaking down the palace gates. A large horde of onlookers, witnessing your brave execution of their long-time brutal dictator, have been pushed to revolt, and they are stampeding to take down the soldiers.</text>
	<unlockCustomShip silent="false">PLAYER_SHIP_ROCKMAN</unlockCustomShip>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Stay and help fight.</text>
		<event>
			<text>It's a violent fight, and there's heavy casualties on both sides, but with your trained military crew you help sway the tide in the civilians' favor. Once the battle is for certain over, the civilians thank you for your help. Most march on to take control of Stonewall's palace, but one Rock, a Crusader who turned on his masters, stays behind. "You have done us a considerable service, and I cannot let this go without thanks. Our kind may finally be free from this oppression, and this could very well be the start. I want to stay behind and keep fighting, but I also know a Federation ship passing through here with such a powerful loadout has a very important mission awaiting them, and they can use all of the manpower they can get."</text>
			<crewMember amount="1" all_skills="2" class="crusader">Ihatsno</crewMember> <!--very poorly made easter egg for ih8ih8sn0w-->
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Leave now.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Hopefully this newfound spark of hope you've started among the Rock people won't be smothered by the reinforcements the other Elders are bound to send. You can't risk your mission any further, so you power up the engines and fly away from the city.</text>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

