<event name="OUTCAST_STORIES" unique="true">
	<text>Orbiting the nearby planet is an old Theocracy mining colony, established to harvest materials from the planet's rings. Now, it seems to have been converted into an Outcast camp, where several Rocks and even a few SSLG agents have gathered.</text>
	<img planet="PLANET_RINGS"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
        <text>Visit the colony.</text>
        <event>
            <text>No one pays you any mind as you dock, so it's safe to assume they must be used to visitors. You enter the antechamber, where you find a small atmospheric fire has been lit and residents sit in a circle around one tall, robed Rockman with spears of yellow paint down his arms who looks to be telling stories.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Join them.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The robed Outcast turns to face you, smiling wide. "Esteemed guests, won't you join us! You're just in time to hear the tales of the Dread Pirate Tuco! Tell me, since you don't seem to be from here, which story would you like to hear?" He presents several options.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Tell the first tale of Tuco, the Vrachos IV Protests.</text>
						<event load="OUTCAST_STORIES_PROTEST"/>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Tell the second tale of Tuco, the Kitpak Slave Camps.</text>
						<event load="OUTCAST_STORIES_SLAVE"/>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Tell the third tale of Tuco, his legacy today.</text>
						<event load="OUTCAST_STORIES_LEGECY"/>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>I'm not familiar with who Tuco is.</text>
						<event>
							<text>"Ahhh, I see. Tuco is a legend, a hero, but most of all, not just one, but many people. It is a title inhereted through honor and circumstance. We Outcasts pay respects to the many Tucos of history, who have always stood in the name of justice, whether that enemy be the fallen Rock-Crystal empire of long ago, or the modern day Theocracy. Now that you know this, would you like to hear one of my stories?"</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Tell the first tale of Tuco, the Vrachos IV Protests.</text>
								<event load="OUTCAST_STORIES_PROTEST"/>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Tell the second tale of Tuco, the Kitpak Slave Camps.</text>
								<event load="OUTCAST_STORIES_SLAVE"/>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Tell the third tale of Tuco, his legacy today.</text>
								<event load="OUTCAST_STORIES_LEGECY"/>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true" req="FEDERATION_DATABASE">
								<text>[Federation Database] See what the database says on Tuco.</text>
								<event>
									<text>The Dread Pirate Tuco, true to what the Outcast claims, is not so much a singular person but rather a title. The original Tuco for which the moniker was derived lived during the days of the archaic Rock-Crystal Empire and fought against Toarde and the other 4 Rock Elders during the collapse of the Empire. While Tuco's side inevitably lost and the Theocracy rose from the ashes of that war, stories of the ventures of Tuco continued to be shared by Rock school-children even after the Elders forbade them from being told. Several Rockmen have picked up the title of Tuco since then, giving the name even more infamy and immortality. The current holder of the title is believed to once have been known as Rowbad, and currently works as a bodyguard for Ocym, the Aquarian co-founder of the Argeonn smuggler clan.</text>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Tell the first tale of Tuco, the Vrachos IV Protests.</text>
