<event name="OUTCAST_STORIES_PROTEST">
	<text>"An excellent choice." The Outcast stretches out his arms to the crowd as you take a seat, then begins to tell his story. "Not too long ago, on the cusp of the revolution, protestors had begun to gather on Vrachos IV, the homeworlds of the Rock species and capital planet of the Theocracy! Though they started peacefully, Stonewall (the residing Elder and leader of the Inquisitions) would not dare have anyone question himself or the other Elders, and so he dispatched his Crusader forces to handle the crowds."</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Among them was a young Outcast whom today we know as Tuco, a fiery spirit who would not let the Theocracy continue to spit in the face of freedom! Soon, the conflict grew so large that the Paladins from Numa V had to be called, a rare but significant show of force from the Elders. So numerous were the arrests made that it was clear executions would be inefficient, and so the leaders of the protests were killed and the rest exiled. Tuco, with nowhere left to go, journeyed with the countless thousands of other Outcasts to the Badlands, where they founded the first of the Outcast settlements that we live in today."</text>
