			</event>
		</choice>
	</event>
</eventList>

<event name="OUTCAST_PROPAGANDA" unique="true">
	<text>A broadcast station established by the SSLG has been constructed near the beacon, just close enough for its propaganda to reach new arrivals. "The era of the Theocracy is over! Rock brothers, put down your holy texts and join us Crystals in our open arms! Welcome the approaching days of the mighty Rock-Crystal Empire once more! The Lost Suns nor the Federation will show you the way, only we can guide you!"</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_SSLG_STATION" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
        <text>Hail and request to use the broadcast to your benefit.</text>
        <event load="OUTCAST_PROPAGANDA_REQUEST"/>
    </choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_CRYSTAL">
        <text>(Crystal Crew) Convince them to aid you.</text>
        <event>
			<text>It's tough breaking through the stubborn nature of a Crystal but you manage to convince them to periodically broadcast lies about your location.</text>
			<modifyPursuit amount="-2"/>
		</event>
    </choice>
    <choice hidden="true" req="hacking" lvl="1">
        <text>(Hacking) Hijack the broadcast.</text>
        <event>
			<text>You take control over the station's signal and replace it with an announcement of your own ship's arrival - at a very different location. The Crystals take notice and aren't pleased, but hopefully by the time they fix it the Rebels will have caught the word.</text>
			<modifyPursuit amount="-2"/>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_CRYSTAL_FIGHT"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
    </choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="hacking" lvl="3">
        <text>(Adv. Hacking) Hijack the broadcast.</text>
        <event>
			<text>You deploy a malicious virus into the station's systems that will periodically replace the broadcast with an announcement of your own ship's arrival - at a very different location. The Crystals shouldn't take notice for a while so hopefully the Rebels will catch the word.</text>
			<modifyPursuit amount="-3"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_CRYSTAL"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
    </choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
        <text>Propaganda of any kind is bad. We have to take down the station.</text>
        <event>
			<text>The Theocracy is vile, yes, but these defamatory lies will only damage the reputation of the Federation with the Outcasts. We can't let these lies be spread!</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_CRYSTAL_FIGHT"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
    </choice>
    <choice>
        <text>Ignore the station.</text>
        <event>
            <text>This propaganda might make some unfavorable accusations about the Federation, but at least it isn't calling the Outcasts to arms against you. Better not to get involved with the SSLG.</text>
            <choice>
                <text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
                <event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
            </choice>
            <choice>
                <text>Do nothing.</text>
                <event/>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>
<eventList name="OUTCAST_PROPAGANDA_REQUEST">
