<event name="OUTCAST_VICTIM" unique="true">
	<text>A small Outcast village appears to be under occupation by slavers, who have chained up several Rockmen but are firing at a band of Outcasts who seemed to have escaped.</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
        <text>Intervene.</text>
        <event>
            <text>You land nearby and walk towards them, when the slavers suddenly drop their weapons and their leader falls to his knees and pleads before you. "Ooooh great Federation Captain you have come to save us from these cruel brutes! They have killed my men and I had no chance but to slaughter their families! It was only self defense! I have restrained them here so they can kill no one else! Please oh please, will you help us arrest these evil men and women?" You look at the Outcasts at the other end of the town who merely shrug.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Aid the Outcasts.</text>
				<event>
					<text>These guys aren't fooling anyone. When the slavers see their "clever trick" has failed they scramble for their guns and prepare to fight you.</text>
					<ship load="SHIP_VICTIM_SLAVER" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Aid the Slavers.</text>
				<event>
					<text>It's pretty obvious the slavers are lying but that doesn't mean you can't take advantage of the situation. You prepare to fight off the remaining Outcast survivors.</text>
					<ship load="SHIP_VICTIM_OUTCAST" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
        <text>Don't get involved.</text>
        <event>
            <text>It's not worth the effort coming between the outcasts and Tiiikaka.</text>
            <choice>
                <text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
                <event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
            </choice>
            <choice>
                <text>Do nothing.</text>
                <event/>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>
<event name="OUTCAST_SLAVERS_WIN">
	<text>"Thank you captain. For a moment I feared you might actually side with the slavers. You have all of our thanks."</text>
	<autoReward level="LOW">item</autoReward>
</event>
<event name="OUTCAST_OUTCAST_WIN">
	<text>"See, I knew you'd follow through in the name of justice! Hooray for the Federation! Three cheers!" The slaver looks around but sees no one is clapping and gives up. "Alright whatever. Take a slave or something I dunno."</text>
	<crewMember amount="1" class="outcast"/>
</event>

<event name="OUTCAST_TEAMWORK" unique="true"> <!--technically hostile but it fits neutral better-->
	<text>As soon as you catch sight of the ship at this beacon you regret coming here. Looks like the Coalition has penetrated into this territory. You promptly receive a hail from the ship.</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
        <text>Respond.</text>
        <event>
            <text>The captain of the vessel, a Slug dressed in a cheap lab coat, appears on the screen. "Now, I know thisss iss unconventional, but the Coalition can wait. I am on a quessst... for SSSSCIENCCCE! Sssspeccifically, I wisssh to underssstand what about the Outcassstsss grantsss them sssuch amplified abilitiesss in the pressssenccce of each other. My own crew is not ssso willing to asssissst me, the lazy bassstardsss, so I requessst you go and obtain a few bodiesss from the nearby Outcassst colony. For pay, of courssse. No one doesss ssshit for free anymore."</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Accept.</text>
				<event>
					<text>Following the directions from the Coalition vessel, you're guided to a small Outcast colony with a few ships docked. Wasting no time, you power up your weapons and engage! No need to target the crew - even after an explosion the resilient bodies of Rockmen will stay intact.</text>
					<ship load="SHIP_OUTCAST_TEAMWORK" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Decline.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Wow, even money couldn't coax you greedy bassstardsss into doing sssomething? What hassss the world come too... Oh well, guessss I have to kill you now."</text>
					<ship load="SHIP_COALITION_GENERIC" hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_HUMAN">
				<text>(Human Crew) "Teamwork makes the dream work."</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Uhhh, what the hell did you jussst sssay to me? Uegh, humansss and their ssstupid cheesssy phrasssess. What doess that have to do with anything anywaysss?"</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Outcasts get their abilities from teamwork.</text>
						<event>
							<text>"What? Teamwork? I've heard of that, but I have yet to identify the genome. Issss that ssome kind of genetic trait ssshared by Outcassstss? I ssshall resssearch thisss further. Thissss hass been a massssive help."</text>
							<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
        <text>Attack pre-emptively.</text>
        <event>
            <text>There's no way you're risking falling into a trap from the Coalition. Arm the weapons!</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_COALITION_GENERIC" hostile="true"/>
            <choice hidden="true">
                <text>Continue...</text>
                <event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
            </choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>

<event name="OUTCAST_ANNOYING" unique="true">
	<text>An outcast vessel is approaching, their captain wearing a bright yellow leotard and carrying a harp in his hand. "Halt, Federation! I hath taken a noble voyage to the lands of the Dynasty and learned from the finest of poets the art of story telling. I demand thee listen to mine tale, or I shall come and squish your puny skull between my thighs!"</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_OUTCAST_FIGHT" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
        <text>Listen to his story.</text>
        <event>
            <text>The Rockman strums his harp, then begins to speak in a strange accent. "My story begins with darkness and a scream, as my infantile body exits the womb of my mother. How I cried! How she cried! We all cried! I think! I don't really know, I was just born. I'm just guessing. People normally cry after childbirth, I think."</text>
			<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue listening.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The outcast isn't off to a great start, but it only gets worse. He takes you through all of the experiences of his early, teenaged, and adult life. He complains of old girlfriends, bad teachers, idiotic co-workers, some weird story about eating one of the statues outside of his church, how he became vegetarian after visiting the Orchids, an affair with a Separatist, and some other even more outlandish stories you're certain are fake.</text>
					<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>He should be almost done.</text>
						<event>
							<text>Somehow, the poet continues all the way past the current day and onto the lives of his children. Most of your crew have already fallen asleep but somehow, by some miracle, the poet finally finishes his story. "I do hope thou enjoyed it! I'll be publishing the written work and even an audiobook soon! Rate it 5 stars if thou liked it! I'm not really sure what else to say!" There's a few moments of awkward silence, but the outcast transfers over some scrap and a weapon as 'thanks' and to help 'encourage' you to promote him to your friends.</text>
							<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
							<autoReward level="HIGH">scrap_only</autoReward>
							<weapon name="RANDOM"/>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Cut him off and leave.</text>
						<event>
							<text>No way you're wasting even more time listen to this weirdo and his life story. Better fight your way out!</text>
							<ship hostile="true"/>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Stop him and try to leave.</text>
				<event>
					<text>No way you're wasting even more time listen to this weirdo and his life story. Better fight your way out!</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
        <text>Sounds like his story is a long one. We better fight through this.</text>
        <event>
            <text>No way you're wasting time listen to this weirdo and his life story. Better fight your way out!</text>
            <ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>

<event name="OUTCAST_CHUNGUS" unique="true">
	<text>A crowd of ships have gathered around a large battleship with a floating sign besides it that reads "Come see the one and only Chung Bungalung, the Rock who lived!" Excited chatter takes place between the different ships, sharing tales of Chung's seemingly impossible escape from the clutches of the Theocracy.</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_OUTCAST_FAT" hostile="false"/>
	<choice>
        <text>Pay the entrance fee.</text>
        <event>
            <text>You're annoyed about having to pay to enter, but it's cheap enough. Inside you see several paintings of a Rockman so overweight that his head has merged with his torso, and a commemorative set of souvenirs of replica bullet casings. A repurposed Anti-Personnel drone greets you. "Welcome to the esteemed home of Mr. Chung Bungalung, the Rockman who Lived!"</text>
			<item_modify>
				<item type="scrap" min="-5" max="-5"/>
			</item_modify>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Follow the drone.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The drone guides you to a new room where you find none other than Chung Bungalung himself. "A renegade?! Wasn't expecting Feds to come here. Greetings! I am Chung Bungalung, the Rockman who Lived!"</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Yeah, I've heard. Why do they call you that anyways?</text>
						<event>
							<text>"Well, you see, it's illegal in the Theocracy to offend a Rock Priest by being ugly, and ugly I very much am! I was sentenced to death, but it takes more than a bullet to stop Chung Bungalug, the Rockman who Lived! They shot me not once, not twice, but five times! Eventually they gave up and simply dumped me out here! I've become a living legend amongst the Outcasts. And, if you can best me in a duel, then I'll even tell you my secret on how I survived the bullets!"</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Challenge him to a duel.</text>
								<event>
									<text>"Haha, now that's what I like to hear. Commence the battle!"</text>
									<ship hostile="true"/>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Continue...</text>
										<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>No thanks.</text>
								<event>
									<text>"Disappointing! Oh well then, I understand. But you'll never learn my secret, haha!"</text>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore the ships.</text>
		<event>
			<text>This all seems like some kind of scam or tourist trap. Not that those are mutually exclusive. No point in stopping here.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="OUTCAST_CHUNGUS_WIN">
	<text>"Congratulations, you have bested me! My secret is yours!" Chung powers down his weapons.</text>
	<clearTriggeredEvent name="BUNGALUNG_WIN"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
        <text>Stop the fight.</text>
        <event>
            <text>Chung leans forward and whispers in your ear; "My secret, is this... my girth."</text>
			<clearTriggeredEvent name="BUNGALUNG_LOSE"/>
			<ship hostile="false"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Your... what?</text>
				<event>
					<text>"HAHAHAH! MY GIRTH! Those dumbasses couldn't penetrate my skull because it was protected by layers upon layers of fat. Now, for being such a good sport and being the first to ever best me in combat, have this!"</text>
					<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
					<augment name="EX_LAB_ROCK_SKIN"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
        </event>
    </choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
        <text>Keep on fighting anyways.</text>
        <event>
            <text>"Wait, wait- what are you doing?!"</text>
        </event>
    </choice>
</event>
<event name="OUTCAST_CHUNGUS_LOSE">
	<text>"It seems you have lost this battle! Alas, you shall not learn my secret. Apologies, captain!"</text>
	<clearTriggeredEvent name="BUNGALUNG_LOSE"/>
	<clearTriggeredEvent name="BUNGALUNG_WIN"/>
	<ship hostile="false"/>
</event>

<event name="OUTCAST_MAKESHIFT" unique="true">
	<text>A small makeshift Tiiikaka outpost has been constructed nearby for holding slaves. Judging from the fact they don't hail you, it's pretty clear they aren't open to trading.</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
        <text>Attack the camp.</text>
        <event>
            <text>Even if they were open to selling to you, you wouldn't care. Slavery is immoral, and you're going to free these people.</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_OUTCAST_MAKESHIFT_SLAVER" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
