<textList name="TEXT_ENCOUNTER_SSLG">
	<text>The SSLG's agents have little beef with the Federation, but they've always been suspicious that it might try to intervene with their movement. One overly cautious ship nearby spots you and isn't taking any chances!</text>
	<text>You catch radio chatter on a nearby SSLG ship and an unseen outpost some distance away. "By the glory of Dianesh, it's so damn boring here. We're supposed to be overthrowing brutal dictators, not sitting on our asses singing kumbaya with a bunch of hippies! Er, hold on. Someone's watching me... oh what the hell, I'll just go kill them and say they were a spy. Finally something to do!"</text>
