<event name="RUWEN_ENCOUNTER_MISSION">
	<text>Ruwen glances at his forearm where an ornate digital watch sits upon his wrist and projects the time into the air. "Erm, yes, sorry. I've gotten carried away with my ramblings again. Where was I? Oh, yes. I have been sent here by Empress Dianesh on an important diplomatic mission to recover a sacred object! Very boring political stuff, you wouldn't care much about it. But what you might care about is a job offer! I am in need of an escort. As you can see, my ship is very poorly armed. I require a ship that is... hum, how to put it... ready to put the fecal matter back up the rectums of those who stand in its path? I think that is how you foreigners say it?"</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Uhm, sure.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Good, because I do like saying that one! I will use it more often. Anyways, you look like an expert fecal-matter-putter-upper. With a small downpayment now and larger reward upon arrival, I request you help deliver me and my crew to an arranged meeting with the Lost Sun Admiral. As long as it's not too much of a burden for you, that is!"</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Accept.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Truly wonderful! You foreigners are so kind! I wish my people acted in such manners, but we keep to ourselves so often I think many of us have forgotten what generosity even means. But that's besides the matter. I've sent the coordinates, just clear the path and we'll be right behind you! Try not to commit too many warcrimes in our presense, heh! But no really, please don't commit any warcrimes."</text>
					<quest event="RUWEN_DESTINATION"/>
					<autoReward level="MED">scrap_only</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Decline.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Oh, terribly disappointing. Never matter, I understand! You foreigners come and go, always busy busy! Well, I'll be here then, waiting I suppose. Idi Tukala! Erm, sorry. That's... that's goodbye in my native language. Apologies."</text>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
