		<text>Stay and watch the meeting from a distance covertly.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You watch as Ruwen approaches a strangely colored Rock vessel. Seems to be a Paladin, a very rare and dangerous segment of the Inquisition usually tasked with protecting important clergy members. Based on the conversation you're eavesdropping in on, Ruwen seems equally confused. "Oh erm... pardon me. I was expecting Admiral Ariadne's envoy to be here. I don't believe I had any business with the Theocracy today!"</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_PALADIN_RUWEN" hostile="false"/> 
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event>
					<text>The fully armored Rockman barely moves as he speaks to Ruwen, his voice bitter. "The traitors whom you were sent to negotiate with have been apprehended by the Theocracy. The Lost Suns are criminals, and it reflects poorly on your Empire when you come into Theocracy territory and begin to make talks of peace with enemies of the Elders. There shall be harsh consequences for these actions."</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event>
							<text>Ruwen gulps nervously, and shifts uncomfortably in his crystalline chair. "Hahah, surely you're joking! Yes, the Lost Suns are your enemies, but it is not as though the Empire is looking to draw arms against the Elders! We merely wish to settle this ongoing feud between the SSLG and Lost Sun forces for occupancies of the Badlands! That is all. No need for hostility."</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event>
									<text>The Rockman squints, his gaze focused firmly on Ruwen. "Do not lie to me. We have already interrogated the criminals for the reason of your meeting. You wish to assist them in their attack on Numa V - in return to gaining access to the waystone device that you wish to rob from us. These are acts of war. The Theocracy might be involved in many other conflicts at this moment, but do not think we will take kindly to such insults." Suddenly, weapons spring from the hull of the Rock ship! They're going to attack Ruwen!</text>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>Interfere.</text>
										<event>
											<text>You won't stand for this. You raise your weapons and engage the Paladin ship.</text>
											<ship hostile="true"/>
											<choice hidden="true">
												<text>Continue...</text>
												<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
											</choice>
										</event>
									</choice>
									<choice hidden="true">
										<text>We can't risk getting involved.</text>
										<event>
											<text>It's cruel, but this was the Empire's blunder, not yours. You can't risk angering the Theocracy like this.</text>
										</event>
									</choice>
								</event>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
