<event name="TURBAN_BOMBING_COALITION">
	<text>There is a palpable feeling of unease in the room, but every attempt to break the tension goes nowhere. Through the silence you can hear the distant thuds and feel the violent shaking as the bombardment of the city above continues without relent. At this rate, nothing will be left. Hours pass, and you're certain the fleet is making progress on your location. Several times footsteps can be heard outside the room, but no one ever enters.</text>
	<modifyPursuit amount="2"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>Argo begins to hum a tune, some old Rock folk-song, but he's interrupted by an announcement over an old radio in the corner of the room. "Attention all those who remain: return to the surface at once and surrender yourselves. Those who have taken refuge in the sewers or ravines will be quickly snuffed out." You remotely check your ship's radar and see a concerningly large new blip appear. Seems the Theocracy has deployed a cruiser vessel of some kind.</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_COALITION_CRUISER" hostile="false"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Stay and protect the sanctuary.</text>
				<event>
					<text>It seems, despite the silence, that the room has unanimously decided to stand together. As the Theocracy search parties draw near, the door to the room is violently torn from its unstable hinges and you soon find your face on the floor with a gun to your head. Barely any sort of fight is put up as the Theocracy outnumbers your group by almost another 10 soldiers. You're drawn out to the surface, where you find the city is now little more than rubble.</text>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event>
							<text>The Theocracy team transporting the group splits you and your crew off from the others, handing you over to the Coalition troops by the side. During the transfer however, Argo breaks free from his restraints and takes down one of the Crusaders. In the panic, your crew escape and make it back to your ship while the survivors draw arms and battle against the Theocracy ground troops. You trust them to hold their own this time, but they won't stand a chance unless you can take down that cruiser! Not like you have a choice, because it's already locked onto your vessel and is approaching fast.</text>
							<ship hostile="true"/>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Try to escape through the sewers.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You and your crew take off through the sewers, trying to avoid capture. There's a few very close calls but you manage to make it back to your ship and slip away without anyone noticing. You know you should feel guilty, but you can't risk your primary mission.</text>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="TURBAN_BOMBING_COALITION_WIN">
	<text>The Coalition Cruiser has been defeated. There's little reason to worry about the wreckage hitting anything - Turban's already at its worst.</text>
	<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>It seems the Theocracy's mission is complete, even if some survived. Most of the ships have jumped away, and visibly the survivors managed to scrape through the fire-fight. Among them is Argo, carrying a bloodied staff typically carried by priests such as he used to be. "I am in no way qualified to speak in such manners, but I think it goes without saying we people of Turban thank you. We Outcasts never expected the Federation to aid us in such a way. Assuming it has survived the bombardment, you should find a Rock cruiser on the landing pads outside of the city. It belongs to me, but I want you to have it. I must stay here and help repair the city. Turban will stand once again, I am certain of it."</text>
			<weapon name="MISSILES_ROCK"/>
			<unlockCustomShip silent="false">PLAYER_SHIP_OUTCAST</unlockCustomShip>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
